    <section name="JBundle - Creating a sample application">
      <p>
      First, <a href="setup.html">setup your jbundle server.</a>
      </p>
      <p>
      Now you can start your java client:<br/>
      </p>
      <code>
      <i>karaf@root&gt;</i> obr:deploy -d 'jbundle-base-screen-control-swing' <i># Load the swing client</i><br/>
      <i>karaf@root&gt;</i> start 'jbundle-base-screen-control-swing' <i># Use this command anytime you want to start the swing client</i><br/>
      </code>
      <p>
      Now, you are ready to get started developing your application. Click on the 'Program Generator' icon.
      If this is your first time using JBundle, start by creating the <a href="example.html">Example application</a>.
      </p>
